# ClaudeCode Integration Workflow

Establish hybrid workflow combining Sean's creative planning with ClaudeCode's efficient execution.

## When to Use ClaudeCode
- Complex feature implementation requiring precision
- Parallel development/testing of multiple approaches  
- When budget efficiency is critical
- Large-scale refactoring or systematic changes

## Workflow Pattern

### Phase 1: Creative Planning (with Claude in Cursor)
- Sean provides context and vision (natural storytelling style)
- Collaborative exploration of approaches and trade-offs
- Identify key decisions and potential challenges
- Document strategy and reasoning

### Phase 2: Specification Creation
Convert planning into structured ClaudeCode specs using IndyDevDan's template:
- High-Level Objective (single clear goal)
- Mid-Level Objective (concrete, measurable steps)
- Implementation Notes (technical constraints)
- Context (beginning/ending file states)
- Low-Level Tasks (ordered, actionable)

### Phase 3: ClaudeCode Execution
- Clean, targeted execution with minimal token usage
- Parallel development when testing multiple approaches
- Focus on implementation, not exploration

### Phase 4: Review and Integration
- Return to Cursor Claude for review and refinement
- Integrate learnings back into project knowledge
- Update memory systems and documentation

## Specification Quality Standards
- [ ] Single, clear high-level objective
- [ ] 3-7 concrete mid-level objectives
- [ ] Complete technical context
- [ ] Ordered, actionable low-level tasks
- [ ] Specific file operations for each task
- [ ] No ambiguous requirements

## Cost Optimization
- Front-load all decision making in Cursor
- Eliminate ambiguity that causes iteration
- Provide complete context upfront
- Enable single-pass execution in ClaudeCode

